{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review — T8 (LLM / prompt structural-completeness probe) [overlay]: CLEAN — no findings. The plan defines an LLM/agent gate system (five code-reading gates + a `source` enum + signed-manifest verdicts), so the overlay applies; I probed it for the five structural-gap classes and found each affirmatively specified (tool-verified against current source).\n\nAffirmations (criteria this chunk satisfies):\n- [T8] No referenced schema/enum left with an undefined value vocabulary. The `source` enum is fully enumerated `{attested|local}` (parent What; S3 fa49; S5 b7fa), and `ref` is `{branch|tag|SHA}` default `origin/main`. S5 b7fa AC explicitly handles an INVALID `--source` value with an actionable error naming the allowed enum — i.e. the vocabulary is both defined and validated at the surface.\n- [T8] The processing/decision rule is co-located with the schema that needs it. The load-bearing rule \"attested signs / local never signs\" is decomposed as a clean producer/enforcer split that each ticket states locally and cross-references: S3 fa49 marks the run unsigned (AC4), S4 30b3 bars signing (AC3) and is the single place the `verified-at-sha:<sha>` manifest step is written, S5 b7fa reflects unsigned in the result (AC2). No orphaned rule.\n- [T8] No counter/state increment with ambiguous placement. The `verified_at_sha` state write has an explicitly named placement + serialization: set-once-per-SHA, overwrite-on-reverify, retire-on-reopen/abandon, serialized through the ticket's event-append / optimistic-concurrency compare-and-set boundary (S4 30b3 What + AC2/AC3, \"NOT verified by inspection\").\n- [T8] Fallbacks for incomplete/failed sub-steps are specified across the chain: unresolvable ref in attested mode → fail closed, no signature (S4 30b3 AC; S1 6d56 AC5); fetch/auth failure → descriptive actionable credential error, attested fails closed / local still runs (S1 6d56 AC5); absent/being-GC'd snapshot dir → ENOENT → re-materialize, never read a partial tree (S3 fa49 AC6); invalid `--source` / unreachable object DB at REBAR_ROOT → clear actionable error, tested (S5 b7fa AC4).\n- [T8] No instruction-locality / pink-elephant antipattern; referenced agents/skills/enums exist and are fully specified (tool-verified). All five named gates resolve to real operations — `review_plan` (mcp_server.py:656, plan_review/__init__.py:50), `verify_completion` (mcp_server.py:635, completion.py:169), `review_code` (mcp_server.py:595, code_review.py:111), `scan_spec` (mcp_server.py:618), and `review_ticket`. The \"EXISTING SIGNED MANIFEST CHANNEL\" is a real shared primitive (`signing.sign_manifest` signing.py:321; `build_manifest`/`manifest_deps`/`manifest_regver` in plan_review/attest.py), and the proposed `verified-at-sha:<sha>` manifest step is structurally consistent with that existing manifest-line family (parsed analogously to `dep <sha> <path>` / `regver`), so it needs no `_canonical_payload`/`PAYLOAD_VERSION` change — the plan's reproducibility/no-prior-signature-breakage claim is well-founded.\n\nScope note (NOT a T8 finding): the standing S3↔S4 seam — plan_review/attest.py's `dependency_hashes()` (attest.py:106-107), `_rehash()` (:191-196), and the ADR-0002 freshness re-check (:325-326) still hashing from `_config.repo_root` (the mutable checkout) rather than the pinned-SHA snapshot — is a real cross-child consistency/dependency-routing concern, but it is a G4 matter (WHO threads the snapshot handle), not an LLM-structural gap: no enum, decision rule, counter, or fallback is left undefined by it. It is already filed on S4 (30b3) and is out of T8's scope.\n\nConclusion: clean chunk for T8 — empty findings list; the LLM/agent gate system's enums, decision rules, state-write placement, fallbacks, and referenced operations are all fully specified and tool-verified."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782531283787888001,"uuid":"a57c5869-6398-4885-8868-5051c7e62d77"}